        <p><b>Oliver Chua</b> born to a rich Chinese family, he was a proverbial child born with a silver spoon. Their fortunes were thought to last for generations. But when he was growing up as a teenager, their family business downtrend and took a 360 degree turn. His father passed away and their fortune collapsed. As a typical Chinese lad, they were trained to be self-reliant and work hard for the money. From being employers to becoming an employee the humbling experience never bothered him.</p>
        <p>
