        </p>
        <p>
            He patiently attended trainings, meetings and functions. It fueled the spark and recharged him. It gave him the courage to do the business. At first he perceived that his reserved (shy) personality was his weakness, but he found out that it would be his strength. Because of that he is easily duplicable. Most people would look up to him and say, “If he (Oliver) can do it, so can I”. His success was not at all a walk in the park. Several hurdles were encountered along the way.
        </p>
        <p>
